evidence: The as-cast alloy has the yield strength of 1240 MPa and a pronounced strain hardening capacity, which results in a good ductilitythe alloy survives 50% reduction without any signs of fracture. Annealing at 1200°C for 24 hours significantly affects the room temperature compression behavior of the Al 0.5 CrNbTi 2 V 0.5 alloy; the yield strength reaches 1340MPa, but the alloy becomes less ductile and fractures after 18.5% height reduction.
The precipitation of Laves phase particle increased room temperature compression yield strength of the alloy from 1240 MPa to 1340 MPa
